8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both BrightEdge and SE Ranking share a solid foundation of core features including Keyword Research, Rank Tracking, Site Audit, Backlink Analysis. Interestingly, both platforms offer nearly identical feature sets. The difference lies more in the implementation quality and depth of each feature rather than feature availability itself. \n\nLooking at user ratings, BrightEdge holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 5/10, while SE Ranking scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, BrightEdge offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Custom, compared to SE Ranking's starting price of $65/mo. Neither platform offers a free plan, so you will need to budget for at least the starting tier from the beginning. Be sure to take advantage of any trial periods they may offer."}]]}]
